  "key": "agtzfmJjb29rYm9va3IPCxIHUmVjaXBlMhjP3AIM",
  "directions": "1.  Preheat oven to 375°F.  Line a 15x10x1\" pan with foil, leaving a 2\" overhang (we usually use a smaller pan to make thicker brownies).  Grease well with 1T butter.\n\n2.  Melt remaining 11T's butter with unsweetened chocolate over a double boiler or in a microwave.  Remove from heat and whisk in sugar, espresso, vanilla, and salt (mixture will be grainy); then add eggs one at a time, whisking until smooth after each addition.\n\n3.  Toss together flour and chocolate chips in a separate bowl.  Add to batter, stirring until just combined.\n\n4.  Spread batter evenly in baking pan and bake in middle of oven until top is firm and edges begin to pull away from sides of pan, about 20 minutes (DO NOT OVER BAKE!).\n\n5.  Cool in pan on rack for 5 minutes, then carefully lift brownies from pan by lifting foil.  cool on rack 10 minutes.  Cut into squares and lift with spatula.",
