  "directions": "Oil bottom and sides of 13x9x2\" pan and dust w/ powdered sugar.\n\nIn large bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.  Soften.\n\nIn 3 qt. saucepan, cook sugar, syrup, hot water & salt over low heat, stirring with wooden spoon until sugar dissolves.  Increase heat to moderate and boil (do not stir) to 240°, ~12 minutes.\n\nPour mix over gelatin.  Stir to dissolve.  Beat on high until tripled, ~6-10 min.\n\nBeat whites to stiff peak.  Add eggs and vanilla to syrup mixture.  Beat until just combined.\n\nPour into pan.  sift 1/4 cup powdered sugar over.  Chill 3 hours to 1 day.\n\nFlip out, cut and toss in powdered sugar.  Will keep 1 week.",
