  "key": "agtzfmJjb29rYm9va3IPCxIHUmVjaXBlMhiVvAUM",
  "directions": "Melt the butter in a saucepan; add the vegetables, cover and sweat on a very low heat for 45 minutes to an hour, or until the vegetables are completely soft.  Add the stock and bring to a boil; simmer gently for a further 15 minutes, no more. Season with sea salt.  (Or, for a quicker version, saute vegetables until translucent, then add stock and boil until potatoes are tender.)\n\nLiquidize in small batches until completely smooth, then pass the mixture through a fine sieve. In the restaurant we would us a chinoise sieve. This is hard work, but the resulting texture is as good as liquid velvet and is what turns this soup from something good into something remarkable.\n\nAlternatively, for a chunkier soup, only puree 3/4 of the soup and mix it with the other 1/4.\n\nStir in the cream and reheat as close to boiling as possible, but stop short or you run the risk of curdling the soup.\n\nServe with a garnish of chopped chives, watercress, bacon and cheese.",
